===


title: ExplainTheSystemsOfTheBailoutFacility
---
<<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita LayingItAllOut>>
Hypolita: Certainly. To your right is a MediStat cryo-recovery pod. 
<<trigger_gesture  ScientitstHypolita ConcedingAPoint>>
Hypolita: Should you befall overwhelming injury, a Science Directory mech will be dispatched to bring you to this pod.
Hypolita: Additionaly, when you enter a cavern or mine, be sure to note the location of the MediStat pod and which organization, if any, will coordinate your rescue.
<<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita LayingItAllOut>>
Hypolita: To your left, is our EquiBap decontamination chamber. Contamination is a constant concern in any cavern you enter upon our planet.
<<trigger_gesture  ScientitstHypolita ConcedingAPoint>>
Hypolita: You'll be familiar with chambers like these on the entrances to the planetary capital.
Hypolita: Be vigilant and track your status if you're contaminated with microbes, plant spores or any other life forms you come in contact with.
<<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita LayingItAllOut>>
Hypolita: In addition to decontaminating you fully, minor infections are treatable with this system.
<<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita ShakeHead>>
Hypolita: If your infections progress to moderate severity, don't use the decontamination chamber. 
Hypolita: The worse your infection, the greater is the risk of killing biomass that has replaced your internal organs' functions. 
<<trigger_gesture  ScientitstHypolita ConcedingAPoint>>
-> You mean it would eat my organ while gradually taking over its failing function, without triggering a massive immune response.
    Hypolita: Precisely, the life of this planet does not alert the immune system to widespread colonization until it's too late. 
    Hypolita: Beyond the confines of this training, which is not long enough for such a fate to befall you, manual biometric tracking is vital. 
    <<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita ShakeHead>>
    Hypolita: It's not a sudden thing, this organ replacement phenomenon's progression. If you monitor biometrics, you need not panic if you're contaminated or infected.
    Hypolita: Don't feel the need to rush back to an EquiBap tank every time you are conaminated. 
    Hypolita: Even minor infections should not be cause for the abortion of your current tasks, so long as you take care to decontaminate on the way back out.
-> Gross. Don't tell me this is going to happen here in your caverns...
    <<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita ShakeHead>>
    Hypolita: No, not to worry. This training is too short for any infection to progress that far. It's gross, but it's important ground to cover.
-> Got it. Thank you, doctor.
Hypolita: Certainly. Now then, straight ahead is a storage room. You'll find my old Stunner Pistol and a key access terminal.
<<trigger_gesture  ScientitstHypolita ConcedingAPoint>>
Hypolita: Do you need me to explain further?
<<add_objective GetKeyAccessForMine01>>
<<activate_objective GetKeyAccessForMine01>>
-> Please do, doctor.
    <<jump HypolitaExplainsHeatGunAndKeyAccess>>
-> No need, I know what to do.
<<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita HandsDownSayingOK>>
Hypolita: Excellent, I'll standby.
===

title: HypolitaExplainsHeatGunAndKeyAccess
---
<<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita HandsDownSayingOK>>
Hypolita: Ok, that Stunner Pistol is standard issue Science Directorate defense weapon, and is powered by standard weapons-grade Magnium-ion cells.
Hypolita: The model is old but it's plenty powerful for self-defense and neutralizing contaminating flora and fauna you'll find in this cavern complex.
<<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita LayingItAllOut>>
Hypolita: The sampling tool is pretty simple to use. Just equip it and point it at a juicy liquid filled alien plant and jab at close range.
Hypolita: Additionaly, when you enter a cavern or mine, be sure to note the location of the MediStat pod and which organization, if any, will coordinate your rescue.
<<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita LayingItAllOut>>
Hypolita: All the mines and caverns of this particular region share a host of possible creatures or organisms, all of which you should manage.
Hypolita: Your pickaxe, light source, hatchet, and stunner pistol all collected, and you're equipped to handle those subterranean tunnels.
Hypolita: Of course you'll have chances to upgrade and get better gear, but this is the core gear needed for this training.
<<trigger_gesture  ScientitstHypolita ConcedingAPoint>>
Hypolita: You'll find it most effective in the upper levels of the caverns here.
Hypolita: The key terminal will grant you key access to the other areas of this cavern complex, through the door to the left of where you entered the atrium.

-> And lower levels?
    <<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita HandsDownSayingOK>>
    Hypolita: This cavern complex doesn't access lower levels. I can fill you in on going into lower levels if you wish to discuss it after the training.
-> Thank you, doctor. I'm ready to proceed.
===

title: HypolitaGivesFurtherInstructionAfterFacility
---
Hypolita: Ok, go and use the Door Access Panel's switch to access that door. The door will automatically unlock and open for you, now you have key access.
-> Will do.
<<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita HandsMidUpPointByPoint>>
Hypolita: My scanners show life-signs just on the other side of the door. It's definitely a couple of Urchins. That's the layman's name anyway. They're immobile,
<<trigger_gesture  ScientitstHypolita ConcedingAPoint>>
Hypolita: but they spew a corrosive gas that has a knack for getting through our best hazard suits, so don't stay close to them for too long. Go ahead and use your 
<<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita HandsDownSayingOK>>
Hypolita: stunner pistol to neutralize them. Again, don't feel the need to rush back to an EquiBap tank every time you are conaminated. Minor infections can be kept from woresening with a antiexobiotic salve.
<<add_objective StunTheTwoUrchins>>
<<activate_objective StunTheTwoUrchins>>
===


title: QuestionsAboutCorePatchTutorial
