-> Core Fruit?
    <<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita LayingItAllOut>>
    Hypolita: Yes, at the center of the next room, the plant growth is centered around the patch of coral-analogues which is where the famous Cores grow. You 
    Hypolita: can usually find two or more just in this cave. This cave is not open to prospectors, so the Core patch is not picked clean.
    <<jump QuestionsAboutCorePatchTutorial>>
-> What are these alien organisms?
    <<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita LayingItAllOut>>
    Hypolita: They are part of the cave's symbiotic system and because they are filled with fluid, they appear a dark red. The two types living in this cave are easy to spot.
    Hypolita: One looks like a pair of kidneys and the other looks a bit like a mushroom. Both red, and pulsating. Not to be confused with the organisms you just stunned, they
    <<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita HandsDownSayingOK>>
    Hypolita: are not going to spew contaminated waste in your face. These liquid sacs can leak contaminant but you can avoid exposure by being gentle.
    <<jump QuestionsAboutCorePatchTutorial>>
-> No, doctor.
<<trigger_gesture ScientistHypolita HandsDownSayingOK>>
Hypolita: Ok, get the Core and samples.
